The paper discusses lattice reduction strategies and their applications in communications and cryptography, which are topics typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also involves the development of upper bounds, which is a common theme in Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents examples of the applications of the improved upper bounds, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
